HEADWORD: Water meadow
<hw>Wa"ter mead"ow</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>A meadow,
or piece of low, flat land, capable of being kept in a state of
fertility by being overflowed with water from some adjoining river or
stream.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water measure</ent>⟦br⟧
